Removed useless import
Made the npm build more clean

Removed depricated use of open() + made port flexibleRemoved the warning to get a clean build:  DeprecationWarning: `open()` is deprecated in mongoose >= 4.11.0 by declaring the boolean value of Mongoclient as true.

What I personally encountered... I was running another server on port 3000, Thus when I was setting up Dronesym, I got an error of port already being in use, So I made a global variable named port, and added string concatenation to console the running port into the terminal. If users already have port 3000 in use, then they could just change the value of variable in /dronesym-node/index.js.
Added missing instruction of running mongod

Most of the people including me forgot to run ```mongod``` in one terminal, and then execute ```mongorestore --db dronesym dronedb/dronesym```, So I've added an instruction step.
Added latest and more supportive version of flask
Added E2E tests for Login authorization 

1. Checks URL redirection vulnerability (security purpose).
2. Checks Server's availability.
3. Checks Login authorization through admin's account.
4. Checks the dashboard appearance on putting correct credentials.
5. Logs out of admin's account 
6. Checks Login authorization through admin's account.
Added character encoding & meta for responsiveness

Made the Login Page responsive

This DroneSym Webapp can now work on small phones, mid-sized phones, large phones, laptops, large laptops, HD TV and even a 4K TV
